      "writtenOn": "2016-05-06T21:44:57Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "very good find, I need to add an explanation as a comment\nit doesn\u0027t just protect mState, it makes sure mState is the right one. This means it protects both calculation of the new state and storing of it in mState.\nOtherwise it\u0027s possible for two threads to (1) calculate old state, switch out (2) update state, calculate new state, lock, assign new state to mState, exit, (1) wake, assign _old_ state to mState, ...",
      "parentUuid": "0d22678a_85608228",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 115,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 115,
        "endChar": 39
